node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. This is a new and dangerous tactic to recruit teens to drive migrants from the US-Mexico border to Houston and other Texas cities — with one video offering $4,500 per person they smuggle. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.title: Mexican cartels are recruiting teens on TikTok to smuggle migrants

node.text: Fifty-three years ago, a government commission investigated civil unrest and racial inequality in America. The results from the "Kerner Report" shocked the country but mostly faded into history. The last surviving member, 90-year-old Fred Harris, shares why.

node.title: A 1968 report called out White racism, but history largely forgot it

node.text: The increase in anti-Asian hate and violence has forced many Asian Americans to have difficult conversations about race and identity. node.text: The April 12 police killing Anthony Thompson Jr. inside of a bathroom at Knoxville's Austin-East Magnet High School has sparked a wave of protests throughout the city. Thompson is the school's fifth student to die at the hands of gun violence this year, and many in the Black community say they've reached a boiling point. We went to the frontlines of demonstrations to speak with activists, teachers, and residents who say they're committed to calling attention to systemic failures plaguing the Black community in Knoxville.

That's why health experts asked the US Food and Drug Administration to wait at least two months after trial participants had been vaccinated before considering whether to give emergency authorization to Covid-19 vaccines. Paul Hodgkins, who pleaded guilty to breaching the Senate chamber during the US Capitol insurrection on January 6, was sentenced to eight months in prison on Monday. The sentence is far less than the 1.5-year prison term that the Justice Department requested. At a hearing Monday, prosecutors argued a longer term would deter future political violence. This case could influence how hundreds of other rioters charged with the same felony are punished.⁠

node.text: With vaccination rates still not at the threshold needed to stop the spread of Covid-19, most Americans who are unprotected will likely contract the rapidly spreading Delta variant, one expert said. "For most people who get this Delta variant, it's going to be the most serious virus that they get in their lifetime in terms of the risk of putting them in the hospital," Dr. Scott Gottlieb, commissioner of the US Food and Drug Administration during the Trump administration, told CBS' "Face the Nation" Sunday. Delta is the most transmissible Covid-19 variant yet, US Surgeon General Dr. Vivek Murthy told CNN, and experts say it is exacerbating the rise in cases among unvaccinated Americans. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠

node.text:
American tennis hopeful Cori "Coco" Gauff will miss the Tokyo Olympics after announcing on Twitter Sunday she tested positive for Covid-19. Kara Eaker, a member of the US gymnastics team at the Tokyo Olympics, has also tested positive for Covid-19 just days before the start of the Games. The Tokyo 2020 Olympics will begin on Friday -- but concern is growing over the danger of Covid spreading, with at least 55 confirmed cases now linked to the Games, including officials and contractors. Neither the International Olympic Committee nor Team USA are requiring athletes to be vaccinated to participate in the Olympic games.⁠
⁠
(📸: Julian Finney/Getty Images)

node.text:
Cocaine disguised as charcoal with a potential street value of up to $41.4 million was seized in a joint operation between Irish and Dutch authorities. The drugs were found inside two shipping containers from South America that arrived at the port of Rotterdam, in the Netherlands, as part of what Irish investigators believe was an attempt to import up to half a ton of cocaine to Ireland, according to the Garda Síochána, Ireland's national police and security service. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠

(📸: Garda National Drugs & Organised Crime Bureau)

node.text: Physicians warn a rise in sexually transmitted disease cases is on the way. But it’s not just because vaccinated singles are ready to mingle again — STDs were on the rise before the pandemic. Reported STDs in the United States reached an all-time high for the sixth consecutive year in 2019, according to the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, with more than 2.5 million cases of chlamydia, gonorrhea and syphilis reported. Tap the link in our bio to learn more about what could contribute to the spike. ⁠
